{
  "title": "Awake, My Soul, And With The Sun",
  "key": "G major",
  "key_root": "G",
  "mode": "major",
  "meter": "4/4",
  "bpm": 100,
  "words": "Thomas Ken, 1674",
  "music": "Genevan Psalter, attr. Louis Bourgeois, c. 1551 Sternhold and Hopkins&#39; Psalter, 1561",
  "tune": "Old 100th",
  "lyrics": {
    "v1": "Awake, my soul, and with the sun Thy daily stage of duty run; Shake off dull sloth, and joyful rise, To pay thy morning sacrifice.",
    "v2": "Thy precious time misspent, redeem, Each present day thy last esteem, Improve thy talent with due care; For the great day thyself prepare.",
    "v3": "By influence of Light divine Let thy own light to others shine. Reflect all Heaven&#39;s propitious ways In ardent love, and cheerful praise.",
    "v4": "In conversation be sincere; Keep conscience as the noontide clear; Think how all seeing God thy ways And all thy secret thoughts surveys.",
    "v5": "Wake, and lift up thyself, my heart, And with the angels bear thy part, Who all night long unwearied sing High praise to the eternal King."
  },
